#N Eater 1 (Fishhook)
#C A 7-cell still life that absorbs gliders without being destroyed.
#C Recovers in 4 generations. In digital logic circuits, eaters terminate
#C unwanted glider streams — they act as signal sinks / ground.
#C The smallest known eater.
